<div style="text-align: center;">
<h3 id="toc0"><span>Act I - Scene IV</span></h3>
</div>
<br />
<em>Spotlight on the bar section of the pub. Lighting is dimmer than Scene I, and the bar-stools are gone. Dana is alone on stage, cleaning glasses with a rag, and then placing them at the end of the bar counter. He does this, humming &quot;Where Everybody Knows Your Name&quot; quietly as he works, for about half a minute.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>HENRY<br />
<em>(yelling from offstage)</em><br />
Hey, Dana, you still there?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(yelling)</em><br />
Yep, just finishing cleaning up!</p>
<p>HENRY<br />
<em>(yelling from offstage)</em><br />
Well, I'm heading home. Michael asked me to remember to turn all the lights off and feed the hornets, so do you mind&#8230;</p>
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(yelling)</em><br />
I've got it.</p>
<p>HENRY<br />
<em>(yelling from offstage)</em><br />
Thanks so much, Night!</p>
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(yelling)</em><br />
G'Night!</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Dana continues to clean glasses, while listening closely. Footsteps can be heard from offstage, getting quieter and quieter, ending with the sound of a door opening, and then closing. On the sound of the door closing, Dana puts down his glass, grabs a set of keys from underneath the bar, and exits the pub. Blackout.</em>
<p><em>Spotlight on a single table with two chairs on either side. Seated in the chairs are Jazz and Brimley. Brimley is in the act of eating a taco, sitting in front of a plate covered in sauce and food particulates. Jazz is holding her head in her hands, sitting in front of a plate of three untouched tacos. Brimley scarfs down his last taco before looking up at Jazz's plate.</em><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
Babe, you haven't even eaten any of your tacos.</p>
<p>JAZZ<br />
&#8230;</p>
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
<em>(slightly louder)</em><br />
Babe, you haven't eaten any of your tacos!</p>
<p>JAZZ<br />
Oh&#8230; what&#8230; sorry.</p>
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
Do you not like tacos, babe? Because I have definitely seen you eat tacos so like, that's really messing with my head, you know?</p>
<p>JAZZ<br />
No, I do&#8230; I'm just&#8230; thinking&#8230; about stuff.</p>
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
Okay but like&#8230; so like&#8230; are you going to eat those?</p>
<p>JAZZ<br />
I&#8230; what?</p>
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
Are you going to eat those tacos, though?</p>
<p>JAZZ<br />
I&#8230;</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Jazz looks like she wants to say something forceful, but backs down at the last second.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>JAZZ<br />
You can have them. I don't care.</p>
<p>BRIMLEY<br />
Sick!</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Brimley grabs Jazz's plate and places it on top of his own. He begins to eat her tacos with as much force as before. Jazz stares at his face for a few seconds, making a slightly more hesitant attempt to say something serious to Brimley, but as before, she stops herself. Resigned, she lets her face fall limp into her palms. Blackout.</em>
<p><em>Lights go up on Dana sneaking across the stage, which is bare, save for a table with a printer, and a desk chair. On the opposite end of the stage, Crystal-INE is standing with their eyes closed, powered off. Dana sneaks over to them, and walks around them a few times, inspecting for an on button or switch.</em><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DANA<br />
Uhh&#8230; Power on.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
&#8230;</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Crystal-INE, power on.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
&#8230;</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Son of a bitch&#8230;</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Dana thinks for a few moments.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(shouting)</em><br />
Crystal-INE!</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
<em>(quickly powering on)</em><br />
What, what's happening? Are we being attacked?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Jesus, sometimes I forget how human you are.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Oh, hello, Dana. Isn't it a bit late for you to still be on site?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
That's not important. I need to see some documents. Do you have access to the Foundation Database?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Of course, could you please give me your access code?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Come on, you know it's me.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
I'm afraid I can't give you any data without your access code.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Ugh&#8230; fine, but&#8230; don't judge me, okay? I didn't think I'd have to use this thing very often.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Just tell me your code.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(sighing)</em><br />
Fluffy little kitty 2, 13, 13</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Heh.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Don't you fucking start.</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Crystal-INE closes their eyes for a few seconds.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Code accepted. What would you like to access?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Show me the files for the North Korea Project.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
I have access to 11 pages of documents relating to the North Korea Project. Would you like me to print them out for you?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Yes&#8230; wait, how does this work? Are you going to like, vomit paper, or something?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
&#8230; We have a printer, Dana.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Oh&#8230; right.</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Crystal-INE closes their eyes for a moment. At the same time, the printer across the stage begins printing out pages. Dana walks over and collects them as they print, flipping through them. After flipping through a few pages, he notices something.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DANA<br />
Wait a second, Crystal-INE, you have access to the security cameras, right?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Yes, however, you are not authorized to view Site-96 footage without permission of-</p>
<p>DANA<br />
No, no, I know, just listen. Can you analyze the footage of the North Korea Project team meetings?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Theoretically, why?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Just, do it, would you?</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Crystal-INE closes their eyes for 4 seconds, before re-opening them.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Done.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
How many members were there on the team?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Six.</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Then how come these documents are all authorized for a five person group?</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
What do you mean?</p>
<p>DANA<br />
In all of these documents here relating to the founding of the team and the allocation of gear and rations, it mentions five people, but I remember there being six people, and it seems like you've confirmed it.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
You're&#8230; right. The administration council only signed off on a team of five individuals, including the project lead. Which means that either all the documentation is wrong&#8230;</p>
<p>DANA<br />
Or somebody was there who didn't belong.</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
Interesting&#8230;</p>
<p>DANA<br />
I've gotta talk to Jazz about this on Monday. She needs to know that something's going on.</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Dana, grabbing the rest of the documents from the printer, runs off stage.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>DANA<br />
<em>(from offstage)</em><br />
Thanks for all the help, Crystal!</p>
<p>CRYSTAL-INE<br />
See you tomorrow, Dana.</p>
</div>
<br />
<em>Crystal-INE returns to the exact spot they were standing in before being woken up, and powers off instantly.</em><br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h3 id="toc1"><span>End Scene</span></h3>
